/**
*Adore OAI Harvester
*Writes harvested OAI Records to XMLTapes
*/

----------------------
Requirements
----------------------
- Java 1.5

----------------------
Installation
----------------------
1. Copy adore-deref to a location of your choosing

2. Configure the following in module.conf:

* module.lib - Define path to lib directory containing project jars (i.e. lib)
* module.src - Define path to src directory containing project source files (i.e. src)

3. Run "ant -f build-standalone.xml build" to build project

----------------------
Harvest
----------------------
run simple.sh to test a simple harvest
run write2tape.sh to test incremental harvesting with project configuration.

Configure a harvest project
===========================
A sample harvest project is available at /etc/harvest/sample, which includes:

harvester.conf - Configuration file for harvester
disk1/ - Directory for all harvested tapes
data/ - Harvested tapes organized by harvesting time
log/ - Harvesting log file



		
